data.title: Anna Maria Perez de Tagle
data.text:
American actress and singer

In this article, the surname is Perez de Tagle.

Anna Maria Francesca Perez de Tagle[2] (born December 23, 1990)[1] is an American actress and singer. She is known for her roles as Ashley Dewitt on Hannah Montana and Ella Pador on Camp Rock and Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam. She also played Miracle Ross on Cake[2] and was in the 2009 film Fame, in which she starred as Joy Moy. In November 2011, she began starring on Broadway in the Godspell revival at the Circle in the Square theater in New York City.

Early life

[edit]

Anna Maria Francesca Enriquez Perez de Tagle was born in San Francisco, California,[1] and is of Filipino ancestry.[2] She is the daughter of TV personality Archie Perez de Tagle, and Evelyn Enriquez. Her grandmother Sylvia La Torre is also an actress and singer.[3]

Personal life

[edit]

She got engaged to her boyfriend, Scott Kline Jr., on November 11, 2018.[4] They were married on June 29, 2019. Actress Uzo Aduba served as her maid of honor.[3] In December 2020, she announced that she was pregnant.[5]
